    ====================================================================
    -It provides your data safety
    -It will make your code less vulnerable
    -We can make our code reusable
    -We can define abstraction and interface

-Method Overloading
 -We cannot have two or more methods within the same class - if the parameters are same
 -How can we make parameters different:
  a) Either by changing the data type of parameters
  b) By Changing the order of parameters
  c) BY changing the count of parameters
 -We also call method overloading as Compile time polymorphism / static polymorphism


  A----------------CAR------------------->B
  i) Either by following the traffic rules
     He will reach the destination safely

  ii) Either by not following the traffic rules
      -He might caught by traffic police
      -He might be fined
      -He might be both caught and fined
      -He might get into some accident
      -He might cause traffic congestion
      -He might hurt some travellers
      -He might reach his destination without any of the above incidents occurring

      // static keyword:
         -If common property VALUE is same for all the objects, make that property static
         -static variables and methods are part of special memory called CMA[Common Memory Allocation]/Permanent Generation/Metaspace
         -We should not call static variables/methods using object reference variables as static does not belong
          to objects
         -We can call Static variables/methods only through Name of the class to which it belongs

         -Internal method calling of non-static methods : Since non-static methods or variables are part of the same object, we can call then directly even though calling by object reference variable is also possible
         -Internal method calling of static method: Since static methods are part same memory[CMA], we can call these methods among each other directly or also through className
         -Static method calling non-static method : We access non-static methods/variables inside static method through objects reference only
         -Non-Static method, calling static method: We can call static method within non-static method using className
         -Local variables cannot be static as they cannot be called using className as they are within the method



